description:
The Irish Pub



Already a surprise festival and theatrical hit internationally, this acclaimed film is a celebration of one of the greatest institutions in Irish society, the public house, or more specifically the traditional Irish publicans who run them. The characters in this exceptionally endearing film all run and own pubs that have been in their families for generations. It's through their individual personalities, warmth, wit and wisdom that we gain an insight into the heart and soul of The Irish Pub.


Theatrical Release Date: 04-Oct-2013
